goals.question: What is the distribution of bird strikes by airport?
goals.rationale: This helps identify which airports have the highest number of bird strikes and can inform decisions on how to mitigate the risk.

goals.question: What is the most common aircraft make and model involved in bird strikes?
goals.rationale: This information can be used to identify which aircraft types are most vulnerable to bird strikes and inform decisions on how to reduce the risk.

goals.question: What is the distribution of damage caused by bird strikes?
goals.rationale: This helps understand the severity of bird strikes and can inform decisions on how to prioritize prevention measures.

goals.question: What is the trend of bird strikes over time?
goals.rationale: This helps identify if there are any patterns or trends in bird strikes over time and can inform decisions on how to allocate resources for prevention measures.

goals.question: What is the distribution of bird strikes by airline operator?
goals.rationale: This helps identify which airline operators have the highest number of bird strikes and can inform decisions on how to mitigate the risk.

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    airport_counts = data['Airport_Name'].value_counts()
    airport_counts.plot(kind='bar')
    plt.xlabel('Airport Name')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Bird Strikes')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of bird strikes by airport?')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
        plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    damage_counts = data['Effect_Amount_of_damage'].value_counts()
    plt.pie(damage_counts, labels=damage_counts.index, autopct='%1.1f%%')
    plt.title("What is the distribution of damage caused by bird strikes?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Flight_Date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Flight_Date'], errors='ignore')
    data_grouped = data.groupby('Flight_Date').size()
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.plot(data_grouped.index, data_grouped.values)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    plt.title("What is the trend of bird strikes over time?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
